UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2383
1 AN ACT relating to the practice of ophthalmology.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 Section 1. KRS 320.410 is amended to read as follows:
4 (1) Ocular devices approved by the federal Food and Drug Administration as a drug,
5 including but not limited to contact lenses, that contain and deliver pharmaceutical
6 agents pursuant to a prescription from a physician or osteopath licensed under KRS
7 Chapter 311 or a licensed optometrist as authorized in KRS 320.240 shall be fitted
8 by an ophthalmologist licensed as a physician under KRS Chapter 311 or an
9 optometrist licensed under this chapter.
10 (2) Ocular devices containing or delivering pharmaceutical agents may be dispensed by
11 a licensed optometrist as authorized in KRS 320.240 or an ophthalmologist licensed
12 as a physician under KRS Chapter 311.
13 (3) [Nothing in ]This section shall not be construed to:
14 (a) Expand the prescriptive authority of an optometrist licensed under this
15 chapter; or
16 (b) Prohibit, limit, or restrict a pharmacist licensed under KRS Chapter 315 from
17 dispensing a prescription for an ocular device that contains a pharmaceutical
18 agent.
